modules.description: This module normalizes UTF-encoded strings into specified Unicode normal forms, supporting UTF-8, UTF-16BE, and UTF-16LE encodings. It operates directly on OCaml strings, converting malformed sequences to the Unicode replacement character. Use it to ensure consistent textual representation across different encodings, such as preparing strings for comparison or storage.

This module normalizes Unicode text according to specified normalization forms (`NFD`, `NFC`, `NFKD`, `NFKC`). It processes Unicode characters incrementally using a stateful normalizer that operates on individual `Uchar.t` values, producing normalized output as `ret` values. It supports streaming input without requiring full in-memory representation, making it suitable for UTF-8 normalization and processing large or fragmented Unicode data.
